Britain's youngest undertaker could be the next star of the X Factor.

Rachael Ryan, 18, has sailed through her audition for Simon Cowell's ITV show and won the panel over when she admitted to having to stop herself singing pop songs to corpses while at work.

The mortician, from Newport, South Wales, first started working part time at her father's undertakers at 13.

