At 16 she was made director of the firm, which is now called Michael G Ryan Son and Daughters Funeral Directors.

'I think they were just a bit surprised when I told them I'm an undertaker,' she said.

'I love my job - I've grown up in the family business and started helping when I was only 13.

'But my real ambition in life is to be a singer - I've been singing since I was just five years old.

'Sometimes I have to stop myself singing in the funeral parlour - I just love it.'

